This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for indoor scene recognition, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature extraction and representation learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a large-scale dataset for object recognition in indoor scenes, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
